The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, July 3: Archies is in talks with Venugopal Dhoot-promoted Videocon for a possible stake sale. Videocon has not directly approached us to buy a stake in Archies, but talks are underway through a middleman, though not necessarily only with Videocon, Archies chairman and managing director Anil Moolchandani said.                            
	 London, July 3: Vodafone today said it would acquire a 70 per cent stake in Ghana Telecom for an estimated 452 million. The firm would buy the stake from the government of Ghana on a debt-free, cash-free basis, implying a total enterprise value for Ghana Telecom of approximately $1.3 billion, Vodafone said in a statement.                            
	 New York, July 3: Tata Groups Indian Hotels today received a fresh dividend payout worth over Rs 50 lakh for its 11.5 per cent stake in luxury hotel chain Orient Express, even as a status quo has prevailed over its business alliance proposal for months now.                            
	 Mumbai, July 3: The mutual fund industry has witnessed a 5.9 per cent drop in its assets in June, buckling under the pressure of the meltdown in the stock market and slow growth in fixed income schemes.                            
	 New Delhi, July 3: The country is likely to face a severe shortage of sugar and pulses by 2021, with supply falling by over half the demand, according to a study by economic think tank ICRIER.                                                                                                                         
